{
  "texts": [
    "As these systems generate content based on vast amounts of data (1, 2, 5), it is possible that the information provided could be misleading or incorrect (18).",
    "This raises concerns about the trustworthiness of AGI-generated medical advice, as well as the potential risks to patients who rely on such guidance.",
    "This discussion has been ongoing since (19) the introduction of smaller pre-trained models (such as BERT or T5 (20)) to healthcare NLP, but it has become a more prominent concern with the rise of LLMs.",
    "For instance, consider a scenario where a patient consults ChatGPT for recommendations on managing their diabetes.",
    "ChatGPT might provide advice based on outdated guidelines, which could lead to inappropriate dietary recommendations or incorrect medication dosages."
  ]
}